side."},{"content":"Place milk, salt, nutmeg and butter into mixing bowl and cook <b>8 min\/100°C\/speed 2<b>."},{"content":"Add egg yolks, 250 g of the semolina and 40 g of the grated cheese and cook <b>4 min\/90°C\/speed 4<b>."},{"content":"Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and cook <b>1-2 min\/90°C\/speed 4<b>, or until semolina is cooked."},{"content":"Place a bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh 40 g of the uncooked semolina into it. Spread half of the uncooked semolina in a thin layer on a silicone bread mat or piece of baking paper (approx  60 x 40 cm). Carefully pour hot semolina mixture on top of the uncooked semolina. Sprinkle remaining 20 g uncooked semolina over hot mixture. Allow to cool (approx. 10 minutes). Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Cut gnocchi into squares (4 cm) and transfer into prepared casserole dish. Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan and bake for 15-20 minutes (200°C), until golden and Parmesan has melted."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Walnut and basil pesto"},{"content":"Place all pesto ingredients into mixing bowl and blend <b>10 sec\/speed 6<b>, or until smooth. Transfer into a sealable container and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Vegetable topping"},{"content":"Place garlic into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add avocado oil, balsamic glaze and water and cook <b>1 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add Brussels sprouts, asparagus, salt and pepper and cook <b>4-6 min\/100°C\/\/speed <b>, or until cooked to your preference."},{"content":"Divide gnocchi between serving bowls and top with a few spoonfuls of pesto. Add Brussels sprouts and asparagus, then drizzle with avocado oil and balsamic glaze before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["<p>If you are in a hurry, sprinkle 20 g uncooked semolina into the greased casserole dish pour hot semolina mixture straight into the dish. Sprinkle with remaining 20 g uncooked semolina and Parmesan and bake as per recipe.<\/p>","We used fine semolina in this recipe. Coarse semolina will also work, although you may need to increase the cooking time in step 4 to ensure that it is cooked through.","When adding basil leaves to the mixing bowl, be sure to add them in handfuls, as individual leaves may not register on the scales.","If you don't have avocado oil, use grapeseed oil, or any other light-flavoured oil.","Top pesto with a layer of olive oil, then store in the refrigerator. Ensure that pesto is always covered with a layer of oil to ensure it doesn't dry out.","Make the pesto and vegetable topping while the gnocchi are baking.","This recipe provides both calcium and vitamin B12, and is a good source of protein."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h 15m","6 portions"]}